<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Practical 4</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="pract4.css">
</head>
<style>
* {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 1em;
}
#main-id {
    background-color: red;
    background-image: linear-gradient(cyan, rgb(68, 0, 255));
    font-size: 36px;
    text-align: center;
    border: 2px solid black;
    padding: 10px;
}
.main-class {
    background-color: aquamarine;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
}
.shadow {
    text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #aaa;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.mixed-orientation {
    writing-mode: sideways-lr;
    text-orientation: mixed;
    background-color: aqua;
    border: 2px solid black;
    height: 350px;
    width: 300px;
    margin: 5px;
    padding: 10px;
}
.vertical-orientation {
    writing-mode: vertical-lr;
    text-orientation: upright;
    background-color: aqua;
    border: 2px solid black;
    height: 350px;
    width: 300px;
    margin: 5px;
    padding: 10px;
}
.transform-right {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
    background-color: blue;
    transform: rotate(20deg);
    margin: 10px 0;
    padding: 10px;
    color: white;
}
.transform-left {
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
    background-color: blue;
    transform: skewX(1.5deg);
    margin: 10px 0;
    padding: 10px;
    color: white;
}
.sticky-position {
    width: 500px;
    height: 500px;
    border: solid black 2px;
    position: sticky;
    top: 10px;
    margin: 20px 0;
    padding: 10px;
}
.absolute-x, .absolute-y, .absolute-z {
    background-color: yellow;
    border: 2px solid black;
    width: 50px;
    height: 50px;
    position: absolute;
    padding: 10px;
}
.absolute-x {
    z-index: 1;
    left: 10px;
    top: 10px;
}

</style>
<body>
    <div id="main-id">Hello I am D2D1</div>
    <div class="main-class">Hello I am in Class 1</div>
    <div class="main-class">Hello I am in Class 2</div>
    <div class="shadow">My Shadow</div>

    <div class="mixed-orientation">
        <h3>Mixed Orientation</h3>
        <p>Hi, this is my practical 4 of web development subject in semester 5 of computer engineering. This is an example of mixed orientation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="vertical-orientation">
        <h3>Vertical Orientation</h3>
        <p>Hi, this is my practical 4 of web development subject in semester 5 of computer engineering. This is an example of vertical orientation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="transform-right">
        <p>Hello I am Right</p>
    </div>

    <div class="transform-left">
        <p>Hello I am Left</p>
    </div>

    <div class="sticky-position">
        <p>Hi, this is my practical 4 of web development subject in semester 5 of computer engineering. This is an example of mixed orientation.</p>
    </div>
     
    <div class="absolute-x">
        <p>X</p>
    </div>

    <div class="absolute-y">
        <p>Y</p>
    </div>

    <div class="absolute-z">
        <p>Z</p>
    </div> 
</body>
</html>
